text: Jacobabad District () is a district of Sindh, Pakistan. According to the 1998 census, 1,425,572 people lived there, of which 24.10% were urban. The city of Jacobabad is the capital of the District. ==Administration== The district is administratively subdivided into the following talukas: * Ghari Khairo Tehsil * Khairo Tehsil * Jacobabad Tehsil * Thull Tehsil == References ==
